<span style="margin-left: 0in;">This points to a more general issue concerning <span class="BoldUnderline"><span style="text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;">this kind of analysis</span></span>. Although it stresses that language makes a difference and that social relations are constructed, it <span class="BoldUnderline"><span style="text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;">leaves underdeveloped the concept of security formation that heavily prestructures the possibilities to “speak” differently through rarifying who can speak security, what security can be spoken about, how one should speak about security</span></span>, and so on. 27</span>



