comprehensive intolerance.”</span> </span>**</span>
<span class="BoldUnderline"><span style="background-attachment: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: lime; background-image: initial; background-origin: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;">Enlist more NATO aid for training Afghan forces</span>. In order to achieve projected levels of growth within the ANSF and to address the three key challenges facing the NTM-A</span>—developing leaders, stemming attrition, and improving literacy rates for 100,000 recruits by summer 2011—<span class="BoldUnderline">mentors, trainers, embedded training teams, and equipment are needed from a great number of NATO members. The U.S. cannot be expected to bear the entire burden of the NTM-A.</span>
